race.description: South West Tools & Industrial Maiden Plate
race.comment: KOMITO (5) should take beating. He debuted at Horsham over 1400m and found the line strongly for second, giving every indication more ground is what he wants. The European bred colt should relish this trip now and with any luck from the wide gate he can go one better. COSMIC (10) has placed in both runs back from a spell, beaten just a head over this track and distance last start. She draws to potentially sit closer and will be hard to hold out. ABBY'S CROSSWORD (9) has had a few chances but is going well, sticking on gamely for second here over 1400m when last seen. This trip should suit now and she can figure. SEA DANGER (3) comes back slightly in trip from a solid 2000m run here last time out. The run prior at Horsham was a close defeat and he'll be staying on well late. HIS LADY BAY (13) was disappointing when hard in the market here last time but should relish the rise in trip.
